<item>
            <title>[LU-13746] lctl llog_print segfault if no log name supplied</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13746</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following command executed on MGS returns a &quot;Segmentation fault&quot;: &lt;em&gt;lctl --device MGS llog_print&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The argument &quot;logname&quot; is mandatory but its presence is not checked. This cause a NULL pointer dereference error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
